15/07/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Defence Minister Vecdi Gonul said on Wednesday (July 14th) that the army is working on plans to train professional soldiers to fight members of the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK). The troops will be deployed in the most troublesome military outposts along the border with Iraq, Gonul explained. Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan was quoted as saying Tuesday that the professional soldiers will serve up to ten years, but did not discuss the size of the future unit. (Zaman - 15/07/10; AP - 14/07/10)
